HEADWORD: Saltigradae
<hw>Sal`ti*gra"dae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Saltigrade</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of
spiders including those which lie in wait and leap upon their prey; the
leaping spiders; called also <altname>Salticidae</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

